# Voice-Based Communication Bot

This repository contains a voice-based communication bot that converts spoken language to text and responds with synthesized speech. It can be used in applications such as virtual assistants, customer service bots, or voice-controlled interfaces.

## Features:
- Converts voice input to text
- Generates a voice response from text
- (Optional)Integration with speech APIs (Google Cloud Speech, Microsoft Azure, etc.)
- Interactive web interface for demo purposes

## Setup Instructions:
1. Clone the repository:
    ```
    git clone https://github.com/your-username/voice-communication-bot.git
    ```
2. Navigate to the project folder:
    ```
    cd voice-communication-bot
    ```
3. Install the required dependencies:
    ```
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    ```

4. Run the application:
    ```
    python app.py
    ```

5. Open a browser and go to `http://127.0.0.1:5000` to use the bot.

## Configuration:
The `config/config.yaml` file contains settings for the speech-to-text and text-to-speech services. You can configure the API keys here.

## Requirements:
- Python 3.x
- Flask
- Google Cloud Speech or Microsoft Azure for speech recognition (or any other API of your choice)
- pyttsx3 for text-to-speech
